How to setup slurm for the a cluster of nodes
- sudo apt install slurm-wlm 
- update the configuration file
- sudo apt install ntp
- use ntp to sync the clocks, (ntp.iitd.ac.in)
- start the ntp service
- now restart the munge service
- now again start the slurm service (make sure permission are set to /var/log/slurm
- Most of the error are just because of not proper permission

